Position: Generative AI Developer
Location: Bangalore, India (Hybrid)
Company: Google

About the Role

We are seeking a highly motivated Generative AI Developer to join our team. You will be working on cutting-edge Google Cloud AI/ML services, building and deploying large-scale AI models, and integrating them into real-world applications. The role requires strong technical expertise in Gen AI frameworks, as well as a deep understanding of machine learning, natural language processing (NLP), and cloud-native development.

Responsibilities

Design, develop, and deploy Generative AI models (LLMs, diffusion models, multimodal AI).

Build scalable AI applications using Google Cloud AI Platform (Vertex AI, PaLM API, Model Garden, AutoML).

Collaborate with product teams to integrate Gen AI into enterprise solutions.

Fine-tune and optimize pre-trained models for specific business use cases.

Work with APIs (REST, gRPC) and build AI-powered microservices.

Ensure responsible AI practices, including bias detection, fairness, and compliance.

Stay updated with the latest AI research and Google DeepMind innovations.

Required Qualifications

Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, AI/ML, Data Science, or related field.

3+ years of experience in machine learning / AI development.

Hands-on experience with TensorFlow, PyTorch, JAX, or HuggingFace Transformers.

Strong knowledge of LLMs (GPT, PaLM, LLaMA, Gemini) and fine-tuning techniques (LoRA, PEFT).

Proficiency in Python, SQL, and cloud-native programming.

Experience deploying AI models using Vertex AI or Kubernetes.

Excellent problem-solving and communication skills.

Preferred Qualifications

Contributions to open-source AI projects.

Experience in multimodal AI (text, image, speech).

Google Cloud certification in Machine Learning / AI Engineering.
